The paper deals with optimization problems and algorithms, which are central topics in computer science. The use of submodular functions is a common technique in optimization, and the paper focuses on a variant of the generalized assignment problem, which is a classic optimization problem. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely categories. The paper also deals with submodular maximization, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the applications mentioned in the abstract suggest that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) may also be a relevant category.
